This PR adds an example demonstrating how to handle request timeouts in Axios using async/await syntax.

Solution

Added a small code snippet showing how to use the timeout option in Axios.

Demonstrated proper error handling with try/catch for requests that exceed the specified timeout.

import axios from 'axios';

async function fetchData() {
  try {
    const response = await axios.get('https://example.com/data', { timeout: 3000 });
    console.log(response.data);
  } catch (error) {
    if (error.code === 'ECONNABORTED') {
      console.error('Request timed out');
    } else {
      console.error('An error occurred:', error.message);
    }
  }
}

fetchData();


Benefits:

Provides a clear and practical example for developers.

Helps prevent unhandled errors due to request timeouts.

Follows best practices for async/await error handling.
